LazyWrite is build to have the best compromise between a good page load and write a complex external data in your page (like Advertising).
This allow you to control when should those data start to render or load.

Advantages
* Increase highly the page load
* Stop freezing client navigator
* Forget iframe calls
* No other library required (like jQuery)
* No change of existing code

How to use:
1. load the lazywrite.js before you start to use 'document.write()' or 'document.writeln()'.
   or use 'LazyWrite.render("holder", "content")' to add your stuff.
2. use 'LazyWrite.start()' to start render or load those resources.

Example: Google AdSense
<script type="text/javascript" src="lazywrite.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript">
    google_ad_client = "ca-pub-5840687392233497";
    google_ad_slot = "9902234827";
    google_ad_width = 728;
    google_ad_height = 90;
    document.write('<script type="text/javascript" src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js"><\/script>');
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
    $(document).ready(LazyWrite.start);  // use jQuery
</script>